&lt;p&gt;The School Nursing Special Needs team work with the special schools in Bradford, Keighley and Craven to support and meet the needs of children and young people with additional needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This Nursing Associate role will be based at Skipton and Keighley.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The School Nursing Special Needs team is a dynamic, innovative and forward thinking team, always looking to make improvements to ensure children and young people, and their families, are provided with the best care and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like a place you would like to work, please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short Listing Date 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Mainprize, Cluster Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address charlotte.mainprize@bdct.nhs.uk Telephone number 07714 270657&lt;/p&gt;
